===化石物種===
Fossils belonging to the genus date back to the <!-- [[Miocene|Miocene]] -->[[中新世|中新世]], with the oldest specimens being found in the <!-- 页面不存在 -->[[Cerro_Azul_Formation|Cerro Azul Formation]] of <!-- [[Argentina|Argentina]] -->[[阿根廷|阿根廷]] and the {{tsl|en|Honda Group, Colombia||Honda Group}} of <!-- [[Colombia|Colombia]] -->[[哥伦比亚|哥伦比亚]].<ref name=Braun2005>{{cite journal | author = Braun, J.K.| year = 2005 | title = Phylogenetic and biogeographic relationships of mouse opossums ''Thylamys'' (Didelphimorphia, Didelphidae) in southern South America | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-mammalogy_2005-02_86_1/page/147| journal = Journal of Mammalogy | volume = 86 | issue = 1 | pages = 147–159 | doi = 10.1644/1545-1542(2005)086<0147:PABROM>2.0.CO;2|display-authors=etal}}</ref> Genetic studies indicate that the genus may have originated around 14 million years ago.<ref name=Steiner2005>{{cite journal | author = Steiner, C.| year = 2005 | title = New DNA data from transthyretin nuclear intron suggest an Oligocene to Miocene diversification of living South American opossums (Marsupialia: Didelphidae) | journal = Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution | volume = 35 | url= | pages = 363–379 | doi = 10.1016/j.ympev.2004.12.013|display-authors=etal | pmid=15804409}}</ref>

Fossil species:<ref name=FWThylamys>[http://fossilworks.org/bridge.pl?a=taxonInfo&taxon_no=39991 ''Thylamys''] at [[Fossilworks|Fossilworks]].org</ref>
* ''T. colombianus'' {{small|Goin 1997}}
* ''T. minutus'' {{small|Goin 1997}}
* ''T. pinei'' {{small|Goin et al. 2000}}

